FBIS3-23163 "jptot010__l94126" JPRS-TOT-94-010-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 10 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA LIBYA Al-Qadhdhafi Denounces Arab "Terrorist Movements" NC0403092494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0750 GMT 4 Mar 94 NC0403092494 Cairo MENA Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Tripoli, 4 Mar (MENA)--Colonel Mu'ammmar al-Qadhdhafi, regarding the disappearance of former Libyan Foreign Minister Mansur al-Kikhya, said that Egypt and Libya are cooperating in an investigation to uncover the facts. He declared: We are concerned about this issue. Al-Qadhdhafi described al-Kikhya as "a Libyan citizen concerned with human rights, not an opposition figure." Al-Qadhdhafi denounced the Arab world's terrorist movements, saying that they have no connection whatever with Islam and are financed and commanded by people abroad. He said Islam is innocent of these terrorist movements. [passage omitted]
